  "text": "When building a homology model, we are in the fortunate situation of having an almost perfect proWle: the known structure of the template. We simply know that a certain alanine sits in the protein core and must therefore not be aligned with a glutamate. Alignment techniques such as SSALN make use of this structural knowledge found in the template [CITATION_1] .",
